Memphis Mayor A C Wharton Jr. has expressed his support for President Obama's efforts to extend tax cuts for the middle class and unemployment benefits. He believes that compromising on the extension of tax cuts for the wealthy in order to preserve middle class tax cuts and sustain unemployment benefits is the right decision. Mayor Wharton emphasizes the importance of pragmatism in making progress and mentions the despair experienced by those who have lost their jobs and confidence. He believes that the extension of benefits and tax cuts will boost morale for struggling families as the economy continues to recover.